Exercise 3-4. In a two’s complement number representation, our version of itoa does not handle the largest negative number,
that is,the value of n equal to −(2wordsize−1). Explain why not. Modify it to print that value correctly, regardless of the
machine on which it runs.

W., Kernighan Brian; Ritchie Dennis. C Programming Language (p. 64). Pearson Education. Kindle Edition.
